<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.185771>
    bibo:endPage "34" ;
    bibo:journal "Zootaxa" ;
    bibo:startPage "27" ;
    bibo:volume "2009" ;
    dc:creator "Ohl, Michael" ;
    dc:date "2009" ;
    dc:title "A colorful new species of the digger wasp genus Pseudoplisus Ashmead from the Southwestern United States (Hymenoptera: Apoidea, Crabronidae)" ;
    fabio:hasPart <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.185772>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.185773>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.185774> ;
    a fabio:JournalArticle .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.185772>
    dc:description "FIGURES 1 – 4. Pseudoplisus willcoxi sp. nov. 1 – 3. male (holotype). 1. Body laterally. 2. Right wings. 3. Head in frontal view. 4. Right midbasitarsus, female, paratype (arrow indicates position of modified anterodistal seta)." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/185772/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.185773>
    dc:description "FIGURES 5 – 6. Pseudoplisus willcoxi sp. nov., male (holotype). 5. Mesosoma in lateral view from left. 6. Illustration of major landmarks and sutures. Details explained in the text. Abbreviations: cl—costal lobe of forewing base; es—episternal sulcus; mp—upper portion of metapleural-propodeal suture; om—omaulus; pl—pronotal lobe; sc—scrobal sulcus; sg—spiracular groove; st—sternaulus; tg—tegula." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/185773/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.185774>
    dc:description "FIGURE 7. Collecting localities of Pseudoplisus willcoxi sp. nov. in the southwestern United States (black dots). The shaded area represents an estimation of the minimum distribution range of this species." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/185774/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

